abstract: "We present empirical evidence of quantization efficiency paradoxes in LLM inference across four NVIDIA GPU architectures (Blackwell, Ada Lovelace, Ampere, and Turing). Through 360+ rigorously-controlled measurements, we discovered that (1) default bitsandbytes INT8 increases energy by 17-147% due to mixed-precision decomposition overhead, (2) NF4 exhibits a crossover threshold at approximately 3.4B parameters that is architecture-independent, and (3) Tesla T4 (Turing) validates the crossover effect across generations. Ablation experiments establish that disabling mixed-precision decomposition recovers +79-98% throughput and -35-41% energy. All data, metadata, and reproducibility artifacts are publicly available via Zenodo DOI 10.5281/zenodo.19647290."
